A general issue with modularity-based clustering approaches is that they may fail to detect communities smaller than a certain size, depending on the graph size. This phenomena is known as the resolution limit (Fortunato & Barthélemy, 2007). This issue is overcame by adding a resolution parameter γ to the modularity formula (Reichardt & Bornholdt, 2006). The parametrized modularity\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
